Listronotus weiseri

(Hustache, 1926).

Widespread in the Americas, from Canada to Argentina and Chile (
O'Brien 1977
, 1981;
O'Brien and Wibmer 1982
;
Wibmer and O'Brien 1986
;
Maes and O'Brien 1990
; Anderson 1992 ). This distribution corresponds to the Nearctic, Neotropical and Andean regions, as well as the South American and Mexican Transition Zones.
